<br>
Bear in mind that before all the class balancing talks it was decided by the majority of EQ Classes that the ONLY classes worth while on a raid was the Cleric, Warrior, Rogue, Enchanter.... all other classes where considered a support class or useless.  <br>
<br>
So therefore about 6 months with all the hybrids and casters having no role in groups or raids... everyone and their cousin make a cleric, rogue, enchanter, or warrior.<br>
<br>
You are experiencing a LOT of backlash from that.. you are not just competing with hybrids but you are also competing with the very large number of ex-casters and hybrids who made warriors and rogues.  Their only choices were to...<br>
<br>
1.  Quit EQ<br>
<br>
2.  Keep playing their useless class... and then bitch and whine.<br>
<br>
3.  Change over to a &quot;needed&quot; class.  Most did this.<br>
<br>
We have essentially reached a point of diminishing returns.  We have so many warriors and rogues now many groups/guilds have all they need... add hybrids as viable alternatives and your competition for a melee spot in a group goes up.  Simple supply and demand in action.<br>
<br>
